Data Licensing — Build-a-Jam

This file documents the licensing status of exercise data in src/data/.
The application source code is licensed separately under MIT (see LICENSE).

IMPORTANT: Two sources below (improvencyclopedia.org and ImprovDB) do not
have clear open licenses. Their data should not be included in a public release
until explicit permission is obtained from the respective owners. See the
per-source sections below for details.

===

learnimprov.com — CC BY-SA 4.0

The improv exercise data in src/data/learnimprov-exercises.json is sourced from
learnimprov.com (https://www.learnimprov.com/) and is licensed under the Creative
Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License.

To view a copy of this license, visit:
  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Under the terms of this license:

  - ATTRIBUTION: You must give appropriate credit to learnimprov.com, provide a
    link to the license, and indicate if changes were made. You may do so in any
    reasonable manner, but not in any way that suggests learnimprov.com endorses
    you or your use.

  - SHAREALIKE: If you remix, transform, or build upon the scraped material, you
    must distribute your contributions under the same CC BY-SA 4.0 license (or a
    compatible license).

  - NO ADDITIONAL RESTRICTIONS: You may not apply legal terms or technological
    measures that legally restrict others from doing anything the license permits.

===

improwiki.com — CC BY-SA 3.0 DE

The improv exercise data in src/data/improwiki-exercises.json is sourced from
improwiki.com (https://improwiki.com/en) and is licensed under the Creative
Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Germany License.

To view a copy of this license, visit:
  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/de/deed.en

Under the terms of this license:

  - ATTRIBUTION: You must give appropriate credit to improwiki.com, provide a
    link to the license, and indicate if changes were made.

  - SHAREALIKE: If you remix, transform, or build upon the scraped material, you
    must distribute your contributions under CC BY-SA 3.0 DE or a compatible
    license (such as CC BY-SA 4.0).

  - NO ADDITIONAL RESTRICTIONS: You may not apply legal terms or technological
    measures that legally restrict others from doing anything the license permits.

===

improvencyclopedia.org — NO CLEAR LICENSE (action required before publishing)

The improv exercise data in src/data/improvencyclopedia-exercises.json is sourced
from improvencyclopedia.org (https://improvencyclopedia.org/). The site's FAQ
describes content as "free for non-commercial use" and asks users to contact the
site before publishing or translating content. This is NOT an open license.

Each exercise entry includes a sourceUrl linking back to the original page for
attribution. Contact the site owner to obtain explicit permission before
including this data in a public release.

===

ImprovDB — NO CLEAR LICENSE (action required before publishing)

The improv exercise data in src/data/improvdb-exercises.json is imported from the
ImprovDB open-source repository (https://github.com/aberonni/improvdb) by Dom
Gemoli. The project describes itself as "open source and free to use" but no
explicit LICENSE file was found in the repository. Without a license file, the
content is under default copyright.

Each exercise entry includes a sourceUrl linking back to improvdb.com for
attribution. Contact the developer (github.com/aberonni) to request a formal
license or explicit written permission before including this data in a public
release.
